{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"fine mesh sieve, jug, bowl, 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, round cookie cutter (8 cm), pastry brush, oven","id":"r138797","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-IAnXhpeV_uM\/XZap3iqaVLI\/AAAAAAAAhV8\/p7hQJ5zULC4XwcPRxA_0dVxttWXMTOJQwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Dg-hzAdag5mxbxEs.png","title":"Mini chicken pies","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"500 g water"},{"content":"2 tsp Chicken stock paste (see Tips)"},{"content":"400 g skinless chicken thigh fillets, cut into pieces (4 x 4 cm)"},{"content":"80 g brown onion, cut into halves"},{"content":"2 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only"},{"content":"40 g salted butter"},{"content":"40 g plain flour"},{"content":"40 g full cream milk"},{"content":"½ tsp salt"},{"content":"1 pinch  ground black pepper"},{"content":"5 sheets ready-made puff pastry (see Tips)"},{"content":"1 egg, lightly beaten"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"6.6 g","fat":"11.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"15.9 g","calories":"821 kJ \/ 195 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place water and stock paste into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and weigh chicken into it then cook <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Stir chicken to ensure even cooking and cook <b>3-5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, until chicken is cooked through."},{"content":"Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set aside to cool. Strain cooking liquid through a fine-mesh sieve into a jug and set aside. Discard any solids. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place cooked chicken into mixing bowl and shred <b>5 sec\/\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place onion and parsley into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b> <strong>.<\/strong> "},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then add butter and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, milk and 150 g of the reserved cooking liquid and cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b> or until thickened."},{"content":"Add salt, pepper and reserved chicken and combine <b>1 min\/\/speed 1<b>. Set aside to cool (approx. 10 minutes). Continue preparing pastry discs."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Using a round cookie cutter (8 cm), cut out discs from pastry sheets (approx. 40). Lightly brush 20 of the discs with egg wash."},{"content":"Place 3 teaspoons of the cooled chicken mixture into the centre of remaining discs, top with an egg-washed disc (egg-washed side facing down) and using a fork, press edges together to seal (see Tips). Place onto prepared baking trays and brush tops with remaining egg wash. Cut a small slit into the top of each pie and bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C) or until pastry is crisp and golden. Allow to cool slightly before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Chicken stock paste recipe.","To make your own pastry please refer to the Quick puff pastry recipe in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em>.","Unbaked chicken pies can be prepared a day in advance and stored in the refrigerator for up to 1 day. Brush with egg wash and bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C) or until pastry is crisp and golden.","Chicken pies can be frozen. Place pies into the freezer on baking trays; when frozen, transfer into a freezable storage container and store in the freezer for up to 1 month. To bake, brush with egg wash, cut a small slit into the top of each pie, then bake from frozen for 20-25 minutes (180°C) or until pastry is crisp and golden."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 20m","20 portions"]}